<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-perfect-squares" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Perfect Squares</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_g8doeouf">
            <p xml:id="auto_6me039tr">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_dfydrkio">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_7afp95lh">
                        1.0 Numbers and Algebra
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_h0h0r5k9">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_ynscqalm">
                        1.3 Quadratic Expressions and Equations
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_dvgnw32r">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_sn26vnor">
                        Derive the quadratic identities from the concept of area
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_qv61ubt5" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_hbyqs0cl">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_bape0f8w" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_isk2s1es">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_xg0eu991" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_p6vwu6wl"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_hufj97ch">
                        <p xml:id="auto_1s6kih5e">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand what perfect square trinomials are and recognize the two perfect square identities: <m>(a+b)^2</m> and <m>(a-b)^2</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_564yfzwy">
                        <p xml:id="auto_jcbh99x8">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Expand perfect squares and factor perfect square trinomials using the identities.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_7y6i2b1d">
                        <p xml:id="auto_brnm32db">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Use perfect square identities to simplify expressions and solve problems more efficiently.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
